This project is a derivative work of remnawave/subscription-page
(https://github.com/remnawave/subscription-page), rewritten from
NestJS/TypeScript to Go (Fiber) to reduce memory footprint and binary
size. The following are ported/re-implemented from the original, with
matching behavior:

- Route handling for the subscription page: shortUuid / clientType
  resolution, app-config route, static asset priority
  (internal/api/handlers, internal/pkg/subpage)
- Middleware chain: request logging, no-robots header, reverse-proxy /
  HTTPS enforcement, real-IP extraction, assets session-cookie check,
  and the anti-probing "kill the TCP connection" behavior on rejected
  or unmatched requests (internal/api/middleware)
- Session cookie JWT issuance/verification and subpage-config UUID
  encryption (AES-256-GCM, iv||tag||ciphertext layout, matching the
  original's Node crypto module output) (internal/pkg/subpage)
- Ignored-header list used when proxying raw subscription responses,
  and the panel API client's request/response shape
  (internal/pkg/subpage, internal/api/handlers)

